{
  "texts": [
    "All 25k train set consist of 399 rows, which is the 70% of the data set.",
    "Then we perform 25,000 classification with decision trees.",
    "The decision tree uses an information gain function 42 to select the variables that give the most accurate classification at each decision step of the tree when partitioning with a complexity control 43. 2.",
    "We selected classification trees with a sensitivity (true positive rates) of at least 55.9%, accuracy of at least 74.5%, R 2 of at least 29.2% on the train set.",
    "These measures were the thresholds of the first quantiles (Q1). 10."
  ]
}